{
  "stem": "23350.4",
  "chunk_idx": 12,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 4.7,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 34,
      "text": "And we never knew what they were going to do with us.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 35,
      "text": "And then after I don't know how many days-- whether it was a week or ten days, I don't know exactly-- they let us down, because we were on the Czech border.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 36,
      "text": "And they marched us into Theresien-- Theresien-- Theresienstadt.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 37,
      "text": "And there we stayed two-- two months until we were liberated by the Russians.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 38,
      "text": "But I was very ill at that time.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 39,
      "text": "I was-- we were standing for this soup, and I was having a couple of spoons of soup, and then suddenly, I collapsed.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 40,
      "text": "I didn't know what happened to me.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 41,
      "text": "They-- the next thing I knew, I was lying on a wooden [PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] bridge, you know-- bunk.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 42,
      "text": "And they were feeding me with salt, pieces of salt, and calcium, which looked like chalk.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 43,
      "text": "It really didn't look like calcium.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 44,
      "text": "It was chalk, it looked like.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 45,
      "text": "And there was so much dysentery and so much illness, and they had all the rooms-- the houses-- were all made into hospitals, because the real hospital was full.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 46,
      "text": "Until at the very end, they-- it was already-- I think it must have been in end of April-- that they sent me to the hospital.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And-- and that was my savior, when I went to the hospital.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "They didn't have any medicine, but there was one doctor.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And he took-- his-- his-- upon himself to look after, to see everybody, how people-- you know, to-- [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] how do you say?",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "To-- to see how they are, you know?",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And he came to my bed, and he saw I'm all alone, have nobody there.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "So he said-- he asked me my name, and I said to him.",
      "word_count": 13
    }
  ],
